===Etymology===
An irregular romanization of the {{bor|en|cmn|-}} pronunciation of {{bor|en|zh|揚子}} and {{m|zh|揚子江|tr=Yángzǐ Jiāng}}, a former name for the lower stretches of the Yangtze derived from {{m|zh|揚子}}{{m|zh|津|tr=Yángzǐjīn}}, a former ferry crossing near [[Yangzhou]], applied by foreign visitors to the entire length of the river. The [[folk etymology]] that it means "Son of the Ocean" derives from the homophonic [[misnomer]] {{m|zh|[[洋]][[子]][[江]]}} which was apparently given to {{w|Matteo Ricci}}, whose posthumously published journals popularized the river in Europe as {{der|en|la|Iansu}} and {{m|la|Iansuchian}}.
